'''Adeola Austin Oyinlade''' is a Nigerian lawyer; human rights and International law expert, international speaker and United Nations’ Peace Ambassador. He is a consultant to the [[African Union Commission]] on the implementation of African Youth Charter .<ref>{{cite web |title=African Union Picks UN Peace Ambassador, Oyinlade  to digitize African Youth Charter: |url=http://ynaija.com/African-union-picks-united-nations-young-ambassador-for-peace-adeola-austin-oyinlade-to-digitize-the-african-youth-charter/ |publisher=Seyi Lawal |accessdate=7 January 2019}}</ref> He has graced the [[United Nations]], African Union and many international organizations’ speaking platforms across many countries of the world. He uses his legal expertise as a tool of social engineering and problem-solving in Nigeria and Africa at large. The social crusader’s work has earned him national and international awards including the International Bar Association (IBA) Human Rights Award 2018 <ref>{{cite web |title=Adeola Oyinlade wins IBA Human Rights Award: |url=https://www.ibanet.org/Article/NewDetail.aspx?ArticleUid=b26ad578-a9db-45db-a486-3c48067ffae5 |publisher=IBA |accessdate=7 January 2019}}</ref> for outstanding contribution by a Legal Practitioner to Human Rights in Rome, Italy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pulse.ng/news/metro/nigerian-lawyer-adeola-oyinlade-wins-international-bar-associations-human-rights/wwckgtn|title=Nigerian lawyer, Adeola Oyinlade, wins International Bar Association’s Human Rights Award 2018|date=2018-10-12|website=www.pulse.ng|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref>

== Early life ==
'''Adeola Austin Oyinlade''' was born on 6 August 1981 in Akure, Akure South Local Government Area of Ondo State, [[Nigeria]] to late Elder M.B.I and Deaconess Florence Oyinlade.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://adeolaaustinoyinlade.blogspot.com/|title=The World of Adeola Austin Oyinlade|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref> Adeola was raised at his father's house at Oke-Aro area of Akure, in Ondo state.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pressreader.com/nigeria/thisday/20181016/281900184178059|title=PressReader.com - Connecting People Through News|website=www.pressreader.com|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref>

While writing his secondary school certificate examination in 1998 at Akure Secondary Commercial School in Akure, he lost his dad, the bread winner of his family .

His radio talent was discovered by the duo of Ayo Omotosho and Ige Jongbo who were ace broadcasters in Akure, Ondo state. He was recommended as a radio presenter to OSRC 96.5FM Akure, in 2001 after passing an auditioning test. After about six years of working on radio (O.S.R.C 96.5 FM and FRCN Positive 102.5 FM both in Akure) between 2001 and 2006, he moved to UNILAG 103.1 FM in Lagos Nigeria after gaining admission to study law at the University of Lagos, where he produced and presented many radio programmes and the award-winning 'Know Your Constitution' later named "Know Your Rights Nigeria’ he designed to simplify laws in force in Nigeria to the understanding of the ordinary people on the street of Lagos and empower them on their rights.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.africa-legal.com/news-detail/service-to-humanity-is-never-in-vain|title=Service to Humanity is Never in Vain|website=www.africa-legal.com|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref>

== Education ==
Adeola Austin Oyinlade completed his Primary school Leaving Certificate at Irotitun Community Primary School, Akure, Ondo state in 1992. He proceeded to C.A.C Adu Memorial High School and Akure Secondary Commercial School, Akure for his Senior Secondary School Education between 1993 and 1998. He sat for the first ever National Examination Council (NECO)  in 2000 at the Community High School, Isharun, Ondo state.

Oyinlade completed his Bachelor of Laws (LL.B) degree at the University of Lagos. He proceeded to the Nigerian Law School and was called into the Nigerian Bar as a Barrister and Solicitor of the Supreme Court of Nigeria. He completed his Master of Laws (LL.M) in [[Human rights|Human Rights]], Laws of International Institutions, Constitutional Law and Administrative Law at the University of Lagos in 2014.

== Legal practice ==
Adeola is the Principal Partner of '''Adeola Oyinlade & Co'''; a fully serviced law firm based in [[Lagos]], Nigeria with special expertise in Litigation; Human Rights; Commercial, Corporate and International Law.

== Human rights promotion and protection ==
The generality of Nigerians dread any form of contact with law enforcement agents. This is largely borne out of ignorance of their rights under the law. Such ignorance is often exploited by police officers and others to intimidate and harass innocent persons. In taking up the challenge of educating Nigerians on their basic rights and providing legal support, Adeola started 'Know Your Constitution' now "Know Your Rights Nigeria" initiative on radio (UNILAG103.1FM) in 2008. In 2012, he founded ''''Constitutional Rights Awareness and Liberty Initiative''';<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kycinitiative.org/about/|title=About Us – CRALI|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref> a Non-Governmental organization with immense contribution to expanding the frontiers of Human Rights, Democracy to the happiness of people in Nigeria.

He has distinguished himself through his courageous stand for human rights and his pro-bono legal services to the poor as a lawyer in the last 10 years advocating equitable, just and fair society and simplifying human rights laws and safeguards to the understanding of ordinary people on the street in local languages (Pidgin, Hausa, Igbo and Yoruba) spoken by over 100 million people .<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenigerianvoice.com/news/271527/nigerian-lawyer-adeola-oyinlade-wins-international-bar-ass.html|title=Nigerian lawyer, Adeola Oyinlade, wins International Bar Association’s Human Rights Award 2018|website=Nigerian Voice|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref>

Through his ‘Know Your Rights Nigeria’ initiative, Mr. Oyinlade gives Nigerians the legal knowledge to keep them fully abreast of the whole gamut of rights available to them, equip them with the information needed to stand and defend them against infraction .<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.africa-legal.com/news-detail/service-to-humanity-is-never-in-vain|title=Service to Humanity is Never in Vain|website=www.africa-legal.com|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref>

In 2016, Oyinlade unveiled downloadable  "Know Your Rights Nigeria" app (Android, iPhone)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.appsng.knowyourright&hl=en_US|title=Know Your Rights Nigeria - Apps on Google Play|website=play.google.com|language=en|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref> and the web version<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://knowyourrightsnigeria.com/home/|title=Home|website=Know Your Rights Nigeria|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref>  which simplify all human rights in force and constitutional safeguards in English, Pidgin, Hausa, Igbo and Yoruba Languages.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nigeriabar.com/2018/10/here-is-why-nigerian-lawyer-won-international-bar-associations-human-rights-award-2018#.XCC59UxFzIU|title=Here is Why Nigerian Lawyer Won International Bar Associations Human Rights Award 2018 {{!}} NigeriaBar|website=www.nigeriabar.com|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref> The first ever human rights empowerment app in Nigeria has platforms where users chat Mr. Oyinlade and his team of over 50 lawyers  daily on human rights issues that arise without monetary charge.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tv360nigeria.com/nigerian-lawyer-adeola-oyinlade-wins-2018-international-bar-associations-human-rights-award/|title=Nigerian lawyer, Adeola Oyinlade, wins 2018 IBA Award|last=Onyedikachi|first=Okponyia|website=TV360 Nigeria|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref> It also has platforms where users can share documentary evidence of abuse anonymously and where they can get connected to agencies, commissions, organizations for help if violated.<ref>{{Citation|last=CGTN Africa|title=Advocacy group in Nigeria creates app to teach people about their legal rights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pxNPDkB88PI|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref>

The app has been useful in Nigeria in uncovering systemic human rights violations in Nigeria. His human rights empowerment innovation has being hailed for its free access,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thisdaylive.com/index.php/2018/04/26/ezekwesili-faults-fg-on-human-rights-violation-backs-mobile-app-launch/|title=Ezekwesili Faults FG on Human Rights Violation, Backs Mobile App Launch|last=admin|date=2018-04-25|website=THISDAYLIVE|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref> speedy dissemination of human rights information,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thecable.ng/app-will-help-know-rights|title=This app will help you know your rights|date=2018-04-24|website=TheCable|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-08}}</ref> anonymity it confers on users, prevalence of Android and other smart phones users, prompt access to legal help, simplification of rights and safeguards in major local languages with over one hundred thousand (100,000) beneficiaries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thenationonlineng.net/lawyer-wins-iba-human-rights-award/|title=Lawyer wins IBA human rights award|date=2018-10-23|website=The Nation Nigeria|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-08}}</ref> The human rights empowerment app by Adeola Austin Oyinlade has been endorsed by national leaders, foreign diplomats and celebrities including the U.S Consul General Lagos; Mr. F. John Bray,<ref>{{Citation|last=US Embassy|title=CG Brays speaks about the Know your rights mobile app.|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rdQQHQ4F9K8|access-date=2019-01-08}}</ref> Co- Founder of Bring Back Our Girls initiative; Dr. Oby Ezekwesili,<ref>{{Citation|last=Know Your Rights Nigeria|title=Dr  Oby Ezekwesili endorses 'Know Your Rights Nigeria' Mobile App|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mu1HTfeU8tY&feature=youtu.be|access-date=2019-01-08}}</ref> Nigerian music sensation; Simi,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/entertainment/music/266460-simi-decorated-as-u-s-human-rights-ambassador.html|title=Simi decorated as U.S. human rights ambassador|date=2018-04-27|website=Premium Times Nigeria|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> Popular Comedians; Akpororo<ref>{{Citation|last=Know Your Rights Nigeria|title=Comedian, Akpororo endorses 'Know Your Rights Nigeria' Mobile App|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ryQDOxHaURY&feature=youtu.be|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>  and Teju BabyFace Oyelakin.<ref>{{Citation|last=Know Your Rights Nigeria|title=Teju BabyFace Oyelakin, King of Talk endorses "Know Your Rights Nigeria' Mobile App|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VbvJRl6QZ_U&feature=youtu.be|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>

He has also taken the human right empowerment initiative to the streets of Lagos where over ten thousand people have been empowered with the knowledge of law where he alongside his team of lawyers demonstrated the relevance of the constitutional provisions to people everyday lives. In 2010, Adeola gave out ten thousand (10,000) copies of the Nigeria's Constitution to people including; the Police, transporters, market women, farmers, artisans among others.<ref>{{Citation|last=Adeola Oyinlade|title=The empowerment of 10,000 Nigerians on their rights and commemoration of the Human Rights Day 2010 i|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JhQ_yWFjgfE|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>

In 2011, Adeola brought legal luminaries together for a two-day Human Rights International Conference in March at the University of Lagos. The ECOWAS Community court of Justice Chief Registrar, Mr. Tony Anene-Maidoh; Mr. [[Femi Falana]] SAN were among resource persons who empowered about 2,000 participants at the conference which was also aired live to millions of radio listeners in Lagos on UNILAG FM. The annual human rights conference has taken place at the Nigeria Institute of Foreign Affairs and also hosted at the U.S Consulate, Lagos, Nigeria.

Mr. Oyinlade’s human rights work has been commended globally<ref>{{Citation|last=News Agency of Nigeria|title=Nigerian wins prestigious int’l human rights award|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nIglWr5FbP8|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>  including the world lawyers body like [[International Bar Association]] (IBA),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newtelegraphng.com/2018/10/nigerian-lawyer-oyinlade-wins-iba-human-rights-award-in-italy/|title=Nigerian lawyer, Oyinlade, wins IBA Human Rights award in Italy|last=Ugah|first=Ndubuisi|date=2018-10-13|website=Newtelegraph|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>  world leaders and governments.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2018/05/us-consul-general-praises-nigerian-youth-setting-know-rights-app/|title=US Consul-General praises Nigerian youth for setting up Know your rights app|last=Warami|first=Urowayino|date=2018-05-09|website=Vanguard News Nigeria|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> For example, the U.S Consul General F. John Bray while giving remarks at the U.S Consulate Lagos in April 2018 said "I want to acknowledge Mr. Adeola Austin Oyinlade and the work he has done to strengthen respect and support for the protection of human rights in Nigeria"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ng.usembassy.gov/remarks-by-u-s-consul-general-f-john-bray-launch-of-expanded-know-your-rights-app/|title=Remarks By U.S. Consul General F. John Bray Launch of Expanded "Know Your Rights" App|date=2018-04-24|website=U.S. Embassy & Consulate in Nigeria|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>   The US Consul General sees his human rights work in Nigeria very key to the needed development in Africa. According to the U.S Envoy, Nigeria is "one of the most important countries on the continent, given its large population, thriving commercial enterprises, and strategic geopolitical location Nigeria is critical to Africa’s prosperity and stability ".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://punchng.com/nigeria-key-to-africas-prosperity-stability-us-3/|title=Nigeria key to Africa’s prosperity, stability –US|last=Published|website=Punch Newspapers|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>

Adeola Oyinlade wins the International Bar Association (IBA) Human Rights Award 2018 in Rome, Italy

At the continental level; through advocacy, Mr. Oyinlade has also proffered solutions to human rights issues in Africa including the Jailed Angolan Activist crisis,<ref>{{Citation|last=TVC News|title=Adeola Austin Oyinlade Speaks on Angolan activists jailed over election protest|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-7ZokueMdwQ|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> jailed Aljazeera journalist Crisis in Egypt,<ref>{{Citation|last=TVC News|title=Interview with Adeola Austin Oyinlade|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R98DkUPKfUM|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> the Central African Republic Crisis, the Congo Democratic Republic Armed conflict, Prison congestion in Nigeria<ref>{{Citation|last=TVC News|title=ADEOLA AUSTIN OYINLADE'S INTERVIEW WITH TVC NEWS|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xO5TJ3WrlK8|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>  among many others.

He has also set up a training unit in Lagos, Nigeria for young lawyers, law students and volunteers to enhance the quality of the empowerment offered locally to victims of human rights in Nigeria.

== Peace building, Advocacy and Public speaking ==
At the regional level, Adeola has worked with the issue of "alternative dispute resolution" and championed peace in the continent of Africa over the years. His main focus in the continent of Africa as a United Nations Peace Ambassador is to involve the parties in dialogue instead of continued conflict. He created a model that shows that reconciliation, settlement and peace-building in Africa is possible especially where large and fresh post conflict wounds still exist. His peace-building work is vital experiences and ideas of the great value for global peace. He has intervened in and proffered solutions to humanitarian crises and armed conflict issues in many African countries with relative impact. His non-violent campaigns include the Libya Peace Talks , Niger and Malian insurgency Crisis,<ref>{{Citation|last=TVC News|title=ADEOLA AUSTIN OYINLADE INTERVIEW WITH TVC NEWS|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EITxSQZerO4|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> South Sudan Crisis , Central African Republic’ Sectarian Violence, South Africa’s xenophobic attacks , Migrant Crises<ref>{{Citation|last=Channels Television|title=Diplomatic Channel: Adeola Oyinlade Speaks On The On-going Migrants Crisis Pt.1|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5iIR3h_R8EE|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>  among many others.

As a public speaker, Adeola has graced United Nations, African Union and other Intergovernmental and international organizations’ speaking platforms in many cities across Nigeria and around the world such as Abuja, Lagos, Addis Ababa, Paris, Nairobi, Baku, Azerbaijan, Rome, Frankfurt and Vienna etc.

Adeola speaking at the 7th UNESCO Youth Forum 2011 in Paris, France in 2011.

In April 2011, He addressed the plenary sessions of the African Union's African Youth Forum 2011 (Pre-AU Summit) on 'Readiness to reform National Laws and Legislation in compliance with the African Youth Charter' in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia; the 7th UNESCO Youth Forum Youth Voice for Change in Paris, France in 2011, on 'Youth-led social innovation in Africa <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.unesco.org/new/fileadmin/MULTIMEDIA/HQ/AFR/pdf/Agenda.pdf|title=UNESCO Youth Forum 2011|last=|first=|date=|website=www.unesco.org|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> '; the UNHABITAT and UNDP co-organized YOUTH 21 Forum 2012 in Nairobi, Kenya on 'Intergenerational Dialogue on Africa, Youth Socio-Economic and Political Participation; the Youth Alliance for Leadership and Development in Africa (YALDA) Conference on 'Legal services and Human Rights Ideas';  the African Union's Youth Experts meetings on the promotion of African Youth Charter; the National Youth Conference on Constitution Review in Abuja in 2012 on 'Evolving a people's constitution: Issues and processes ’; He delivered a paper titled Freedom of Information in Nigeria; Challenges and way out   at the University of Lagos and University of Oxford, UK 1st West African Regional Round of the Price Media Law Moot Court Competition Conference on 6 February 2017 at the Nigeria Institute of Advanced Legal Studies, University of Lagos, Nigeria  and many others.

As a law expert and Public Affairs Analyst, Adeola has featured regularly and aired his opinion on issues of different thematic areas on local and international media such as Television Continental (TVC News), Channels Television,<ref>{{Citation|last=Channels Television|title=Diplomatic Channel: Adeola Oyinlade Speaks On The On-going Migrants Crisis Pt.2|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cEQbDx0hcLM|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> BBC,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/yoruba/afrika-46507826|title='Àìbọ̀wọ̀ fẹ́tọ̀ọ́ ọmọnìyàn ló ń fa wàhálà Bokoharam, Shiite'|date=2018-12-10|work=BBC News Yorùbá|access-date=2019-01-12|language=en-GB}}</ref> IBA TV,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibanet.org/Conferences/296597511.aspx|title=IBA - Adeola Austin Oyinlade|website=www.ibanet.org|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> China Global Television,<ref>{{Citation|last=CGTN Africa|title=Advocacy group in Nigeria creates app to teach people about their legal rights|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pxNPDkB88PI|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> TV 360 Nigeria<ref>{{Citation|last=TV360NIGERIA|title=NGO launches application|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NNxlLGO4fAw&feature=youtu.be|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>  among others.

He has written many articles<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://allafrica.com/stories/201408182643.html|title=Nigeria: Oyinlade - Ebola: How Intellectual Laziness Stalls Development|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>  and spoken<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newmediagov.ng/speaker/adeola-oyinlade/|title=Oyinlade speaks at New Media Conference|last=|first=|date=|website=|language=en-US|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>  at several symposia<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.africanpreneurs.com/meet-one-of-our-speakers-legal-consultant-and-united-nations-ambassador-for-peace/|title=Meet one of our Speakers: Legal Consultant and United Nations Ambassador for Peace|last=Mary|date=2015-11-20|website=Africanpreneurs|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>  on national issues including good governance , peace building,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://olatundesamson.com/blog/adeola-austin-oyinlade/|title=Realization of a Better World - Adeola Austin Oyinlade|date=2016-11-20|website=Idea, Innovation, Impact|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> rule of law,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://omojuwa.com/2015/03/re-no-waiting-at-polling-booths-after-voting-by-adeola-austin-oyinlade/|title=Re: No Waiting At Polling Booths After Voting By Adeola Austin Oyinlade|date=2015-03-20|website=OMOJUWA.COM|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> anti corruption, security , constitutionalism, ICC and African leadership,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dailypost.ng/2013/10/09/adeola-austin-oyinlade-african-union-summit-justice-not-only-for-the-plaintiff-but-also-for-the-defendant/|title=Adeola Austin Oyinlade: African Union Summit: Justice, not only for the plaintiff, but also for the defendant|last=Staff|first=Daily Post|date=2013-10-09|website=Daily Post Nigeria|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> Nigeria-US relations<ref>{{Citation|last=TVC News Nigeria|title=BFS BIG STORY ADEOLA AUSTIN OYINLADE JAN 15|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1h3ToXDHoxg|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>  and many others.

== Youth and Global Development ==
Adeola has consistently mentored Nigerian youth in areas of youth policy, human rights, democracy for over a decade and he is regularly invited to speak at youth fora within and outside Nigeria.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ynaija.com/african-union-picks-united-nations-young-ambassador-for-peace-adeola-austin-oyinlade-to-digitize-the-african-youth-charter/|title="Know your rights" - African Union picks Adeola Austin Oyinlade to digitize the African Youth Charter » YNaija|date=2012-02-04|website=YNaija|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> As a resource person to the African Union Commission (Youth Division) on the implementation of African Youth Charter , he has offered his technical expertise to the continental body on how to use African Youth Charter as a tool of accelerating youth empowerment for sustainable development in Africa.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nli-global.org/african-union-picks-nli-associate-adeola-austin-oyinlade-to-digitize-and-popularize-african-youth-charter/|title=African Union Picks NLI Associate, Adeola Austin Oyinlade, to Digitize and Popularize African Youth Charter {{!}} NLI|website=www.nli-global.org|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>

He was also appointed by the African Union Commission in 2012 as a consultant to Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) Secretariat on youth development data covering 14 West African countries in compliance with the implementation of the African Union Youth Decade Plan of Action.

Adeola is also a co-founder<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.afrinype.org/amo-team/adeola-austin-oyinlade/|title=Adeola Austin Oyinlade|website=The African Network of Youth Policy Experts|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>  of the African Network of Youth Policy Experts<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ccme.org.ma/en/media-and-migration/38315|title=CCME - New Network for Youth Policy Experts in Africa Launched in Baku, Azerbaijan|last=CCME|website=www.ccme.org.ma|language=fr-fr|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>  launched in Baku, Azerbaijan in October 2014. The international organisation is working on youth policy issues in Africa.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2014/11/143588/new-network-for-youth-policy-experts-in-africa-launched-in-baku-azerbaijan/|title=New Network for Youth Policy Experts in Africa Launched in Baku, Azerbaijan|last=News|first=Morocco World|date=2014-11-09|website=Morocco World News|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> His passion for national and international development has brought him under the same roof with many national and international leaders such as the then UN Secretary General; Mr. Ban Ki-Moon, Mr. Thabo Mbeki among other dignitaries.

Adeola speaking at the International Bar Association Conference in Rome, Italy

His contribution and 'interest in and support of the United Nations' was acknowledged and commended by Mr. Ban Ki-Moon, United Nations Secretary General. His UN-recognized commitment to the development of the then Millennium Development Goals (MDGs) through his writings include; 'Millennium Development Goals; obstacles and ways of tackling them' in 2007, 'Contribution of Higher Institutions to achieving the Millennium Development Goals' in 2008 and 'importance and benefits of promoting MDGs through football tournaments' in 2009 with a minute video linking the [[Millennium Development Goals|MDG]]<nowiki/>s with the spirit of football where goals count and a call on everyone to score those goals .<ref>{{Citation|last=MyOndoStateTV|title=Sunshine Youth Ambassador speaks on UN's MDG|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MlAS3CxgUfY|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>

He is an advocate of Sustainable Development Goal 16;<ref>{{Citation|last=TVC News|title=ADEOLA OYINLADE  INTERVIEW ON TVC NEWS|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cg3u7t-s8yU&t=7s|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> Peace, Justice and strong institution with interest and support on how the United Nations<ref>{{Citation|last=TVC News|title=Adeola Austin Oyinlade speaks on search for Ban Ki-Moon successor|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CCCb5v0a-W8|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>  can achieve global peace and security.

== Achievements and awards ==

* In May 2009, he was named the 'Youth Achiever', by the African Newspaper of Nigeria Plc, Saturday Tribune in Nigeria for educating Nigerians on their rights and for his 'interest in and support of the United Nations' through his series of research carried out on MDGs (See page 39 of the Saturday Tribune published on 30 May 2009)
* In May 2010, he was commissioned as the United Nations Young Ambassador for Peace for his immense contribution and campaign as a young Nigerian  promoting peace in Nigeria<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.upf.org/united-nations/international-day-of-families/2010/2761-award-dinner-planned-for-day-of-families-in-lagos|title=Day of Families Celebrated in Lagos - Universal Peace Federation|website=www.upf.org|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>
* In August 2010, he was named the 'Sunshine Youth Ambassador' by the Citizen Reporters; a recognition for the Ondo state great and illustrious sons and daughters in Nigeria for his excellence, passion and dedication to the service of humanity via 'the Know Your Constitution' project.
* n October 2010, he was selected for the Nigeria Leadership Initiative's future Leaders Fellowship. Nigeria Leadership Initiative is a member of the Aspen Global Leadership Network.. Same year, he was appointed the Youth Coordinator of the Maiden edition of Kuramo Conference 2010[29] by the Lagos state Government.
* In November 2010, Adeola Oyinlade was declared winner of the 7th Annual Nigerian Youth Leadership Awards, LEAP AFRICA Awards, November 2010, Lagos, Nigeria for being an agent of change by using law as a tool of problem-solving in Nigeria.
* For being the voice of the voiceless in Nigeria via his 'Know Your Constitution' project, Adeola was described as the 'Face of the Future' by the Westerner Magazine. (See vol.2 No.34 edition of the Westerner Magazine published on 29 November 2010 in Nigeria)
* As a UN peace Ambassador promoting respect for human rights, offering probono legal services to the poor, he was described as 'A Man of the People' by NEXT Newspaper. (See Page 19, Tuesday edition of Next Newspaper published on 21 December 2010 in Lagos, Nigeria)
* In April and November 2011, he was invited by the African Union to facilitate African Youth Forum sessions and Youth Experts meeting respectively as a youth expert.
* IIP DIGITAL of the US Department of State website, Washington DC, United States in May 2011 featured Adeola on its site 'for helping Nigerians to know their rights' and his contribution towards the development of Africa. Same 2011, he was selected as the only youth judge of the prestigious annual Nigerian Youth Leadership Awards by LEAP Africa
* He won the Democracy and Rule of Law Category of the Top 12 National Youth Awards of the Federal Ministry of Youth Development and Young Star Foundation, Abuja, Nigeria in November 2011.
* In 2011, he was a Finalist, Bremen Peace Awards 2011 of Threshold Foundation for Exemplary Commitments to Justice, Peace and Integrity of Creation in Germany for "taking the legal path to justice" in Nigeria .<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dieschwelle.de/uploads/tx_news/Friedenspreis_2011.pdf|title="taking the legal path to justice" in Nigeria; Page 33|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>
* In March 2012, UNDP and UNHABITAT selected Adeola alongside the Benin Republic Permanent Representative to the UN to lead a session on Intergenerational Dialogue on Africa, Youth Socio-Economic and Political Participation. At the UN House in Kenya. Nairobi. Same year, he was appointed by the African Union Commission to ECOWAS Secretariat in implementing a project in line with the AU Youth Decade Plan of Action.
* In 2013, he was selected by the United Nations Alliance of Civilizations  alongside other young leaders across the world to meet the UN Secretary General, Mr. Ban Ki-Moon at the 5th UNAOC Forum in Vienna, Austria .
* In 2013, he was named a member of the Technical Sub-Committee on Volunteers for the World Economic Forum on Africa, Nigeria 2014
* In 2014, he was invited alongside his Colleague from Morocco, Karima Rhanem, as co-Founders of the African Network of Youth Policy Experts to launch the network at the UN Backed First Global Forum on Youth Policy anchored by Mr. Ahmad Alhendawi, the United Nations Secretary-General Envoy on Youth in Baku Azerbaijan .<ref>{{Citation|last=African Network of Youth Policy Experts|title=Launch of ANYPE at UN Global Forum on Youth Policies|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WOSTPTK5AsE|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>
* In December 2014, Youth Action Network for Human Rights made a 13-minute documentary in commemoration of International Human Rights Day 2014 by profiling Adeola's work to inspire youth across the world in taking the lead in human rights promotion and protection .<ref>{{Citation|last=Global Network for Youth Rights Experts|title=Human Rights Day 2014 Commemoration: A Documentary Inspiring Youth to Lead|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AMn1xpDCYrA|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>
* In January 2015, he was appointed by the Commonwealth Youth Council' as its (CYC) Youth Campaign Against Election Violence (Y-CAEV) Ambassador in Nigeria.[43]
* In 2015, he was selected as the Crans Montana Forum New Leader Fellow, Geneva, Switzerland. 
* Adeola Austin Oyinlade was named among Top Under 40 CEOs in Nigeria  <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://olatundesamson.com/blog/under-40-ceos-in-nigeria/|title=Under 40 CEOs in Nigeria|website=Idea, Innovation, Impact|language=en-US|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>
* Legal Personality of the Week courtesy THISDAY Newspapers; a leading daily Newspaper in Nigeria published on 4 December 2018.
* In October 2018, Mr. Oyinlade was declared winner of the International Bar Association (IBA) Human Rights Award<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://guardian.ng/appointments/adeola-oyinlade-wins-iba-2018-human-rights-honour|title=Adeola Oyinlade wins IBA 2018 human rights honour|last=|first=|date=|website=The Guardian|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>  for Outstanding Contribution by a Legal Practitioner to Human Rights in Rome, Italy.<ref>{{Citation|last=Cray Tv Nigeria|title=Adeola Austin Oyinlade, wins IBA Human Rights Award 2018 - (Award Presentation & Acceptance Speech)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1kPPd3d3DE8|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref> He gave an historic acceptance speech which earned him standing ovation from all legal experts across the world who gathered at Roma Convention Center La Nuvola, Rome Italy  (Watch His acceptance video)<ref>{{Citation|last=Association|first=International Bar|title=Adeola Oyinlade - Human Rights Award 2018 acceptance speech|date=2018-11-01|url=https://vimeo.com/298427234|access-date=2019-01-12}}</ref>

